<TITLE> AL, BNP set up relief funds </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  The Awami League and the BNP have set up relief funds for cyclone-hit people, the parties said in separate statements Wednesday. In a statement, Awami League's acting president Zillur Rahman and general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam sought contributions of workers, leaders and other people of the country to the relief fund. Cash, bank cheques or drafts could be sent to the account No. 010212100086931 of Mercantile Bank's Dhanmondi branch. Relief materials will be received at the party president's Dhanmondi office from 11am to 2pm and from 4pm to 8pm every day, the statement said. The BNP, led by Khandaker Delwar Hossain, formed an 11-member relief committee Wednesday. Goyeshwar Chandra Roy, convener of the committee, told bdnews24.com that the 11-member body was formed by Delwar and that some more members have been included to facilitate operations. Rizvi Ahmed has been made the member secretary. In a press briefing in Mongla, president of the Communist Party of Bangladesh Manjurul Ahsan Khan said the party had distributed Tk 5 lakh to cyclone survivors until Nov 21. He said the party opened a gruel kitchen in Swarankhola and started collecting warm clothes for winter. Dhaka University Teachers Association held a meeting Wednesday to make a plan of action for cyclone survivors. The meeting, chaired by acting DUTA president Professor Tajmeri SA Islam, decided to pay Tk 3 lakh from the DUTA relief fund. In a statement, DUTA said three relief teams would go to the cyclone-affected areas with relief materials shortly. It also called on students, teachers and employees to send money to the fund with the account No. 61181180 of Sonali Bank's Dhaka University campus branch. bdnews24.
